Aside from their literal meanings, there are important reasons for not interpreting these two words as quantiﬁers. First, their truth conditions are not equivalent to those of real quantiﬁers. In the following examples someone has just killed an anaconda and upon seeing it, utters 16a. Someone takes a piece of it, and after the purchase of the remainder the content of 16a is reafﬁrmed as 16b:

16. a. ’a´ oo´ i

