“That is ’ı´saabi ‘s daughter. Ko´ ’oı´’s son being the

same.”

Here the juxtaposition makes it clear that ’ı´saabi is Ko´ ’oı´’s son.
Very rarely, one encounters multiple modiﬁcation in natural discourse and elicited material. A typical example is as follows:

38. gahio´ o

